## What shipped

Consolidated the three session #2 pre-archive assertions into a single Go-enforced registry in `sudd-go/internal/auto/checks.go`. The runner now invokes every registered check after the CLI subprocess exits and before accepting DONE; any failure downgrades the outcome to STUCK, reverts `archive/{id}_DONE/` → `stuck/{id}/`, and writes a `## Pre-Archive Check Failures` section into `STUCK_REPORT.md`. `LessonRecorded` rewritten from `bytes.Contains` to a structural line scanner (heading form + ≥3 contiguous body lines). `MoveStuckToActive` no longer deletes `STUCK_REPORT.md`. `sudd doctor` gained a `Checks` row listing all N registered checks (flags `(DISABLED via SUDD_PRE_ARCHIVE_CHECKS=off)` when the kill-switch is set).

## Verification

- `go test ./... -count=1` — all 8 packages green
- `./bin/sudd doctor --fresh` — `Checks ✓ pre-archive check registry — 3 registered: LessonRecorded, TasksAllChecked, SummaryHasCanonicalHeadings`
- 22 historical `lessons.md` entries all pass `TestLessonsMdAllEntriesStructural`
- Integration tests prove DONE→STUCK downgrade, archive revert, kill-switch, and happy-path baseline

